[We are greatful for the clarifications. I suppose some of us will not
rest easily until we know that human infections being diagnosed in
the eastern U.S. as St. Louis encephalitis and birds with antibody
identified as being anti-St. Louis encephalitis virus do not represent
infections with West Nile virus. Not much of a chance of that, of
course, but still it is worrisome. - Mod.CHC]
